<p>I want to show a file explorer from my HD in an IFrame which is in a MVC View. The problem is that i'm passing a string with the absolute path to the View and setting it in the src attribute, but in the execution, is interpreting that path as a View name. Of course,  it explodes cause there's no Controller with that name. I attached the controller and the view code. What can i do to force the iframe to just show the absolute path?</p>  <p>Controller Code</p>  <pre><code>public ActionResult ReportsFileExplorer() {     var path = (!string.IsNullOrEmpty(ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["EodReportsPath"])                    &amp;&amp; System.IO.Directory.Exists(ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["EodReportsPath"]))?              ConfigurationManager.AppSettings["EodReportsPath"]              : "";     path = String.Concat("file:///", path.Replace("\\\\","\\"));     return View(path); } </code></pre>  <p>View Code</p>  <pre><code>@using System.Configuration @using System.Web.Optimization @using ReportViewerForMvc; @model string @{      ViewBag.Title = "Reports";      Layout = "~/Areas/Authorization/Views/Shared/Layout.cshtml";  }  @section PageTitle {     &lt;h5 class="page-title"&gt;Reports&lt;/h5&gt; }  &lt;div id="anotherRoot"&gt;     &lt;iframe src="@Model"&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;  </code></pre>